# Unit Conversion API

A simple REST API that converts values between different units of measurement. Built with ASP.NET Core.

You can use it to convert things like meters to feet, Celsius to Fahrenheit, or kilograms to pounds — just send a GET request with the values you want to convert.

## How to Run

1. Make sure you have .NET SDK installed on your machine
2. Clone this repository
3. Navigate into the UnitConversionApi folder in your terminal
4. Run:

dotnet run

5. The API starts at http://localhost:5259

## Example Requests

Convert 10 meters to feet:
http://localhost:5259/api/convert?from=meters&to=feet&value=10

Convert 100 Celsius to Fahrenheit:
http://localhost:5259/api/convert?from=celsius&to=fahrenheit&value=100

Convert 70kg to pounds:
http://localhost:5259/api/convert?from=kg&to=lbs&value=70

## Supported Categories

Length: meters, km, feet, miles, inches, cm, yards, mm
Temperature: celsius, fahrenheit, kelvin
Weight: kg, pounds, grams, ounces, tonnes
Speed: km/h, mph, m/s, knots
Area: sqm, sqft, acres, hectares

## Project Structure

Controllers handles incoming API requests
Models defines the structure of requests and responses
Services contains all the conversion logic
Program.cs wires everything together on startup

## Notes

Adding a new unit is easy — just add one line to the dictionary in ConversionService.cs with the unit name and its conversion factor.

Temperature is handled differently from other units because Celsius, Fahrenheit and Kelvin have different starting points, so simple multiplication does not work.